'''The French National Sequencing Center''' ('''Genoscope''') was created in 1996 in [[Évry, Essonne|Évry]], [[France]]. It has been involved in the [[DNA sequencing|sequencing]] of the [[human genome]]. The center's name is meant to personify what it is to be a gene.
